In statistics and quantitative research methodology, a sample is a set of individuals or objects collected or selected from a statistical population by a defined procedure.[1] The elements of a sample are known as sample points, sampling units or observations. When conceived as a data set, a sample is often denoted by capital roman letters such 



        X


    {\displaystyle X}

 and 



        Y


    {\displaystyle Y}

, with its elements expressed in lower-case (e.g., 




          x

            3




    {\displaystyle x_{3}}

) and the sample size denoted by the letter 



        n


    {\displaystyle n}

.[2]
